title: 'Some will go hungry, some will starve': Global rice shortages feared after India bans exports
description: The Indian government has banned the export of non-basmati white rice - trigging fears of shortages and price rises across the world.

title: Five tonnes of cocaine worth £737m seized in Italy's biggest-ever drugs bust
description: Five tonnes of cocaine with a street value of £737m have been seized from a "suspicious" fishing boat near Sicily.

title: Sharks could be eating dumped cocaine and acting 'crazy,' scientists say
description: Sharks may be consuming cocaine dumped in the waters off Florida and it could be making them act in "crazy" ways, scientists have said.

title: The 'lioness' on the loose in Berlin isn't what we first thought
description: Officers scouring the outskirts of Berlin for a lioness now believe the mysterious animal is actually a wild boar.

title: Ambassador criticised 'sarcastic' Zelenskyy in Sky News interview days before sacking
description: Ukraine's Volodymyr Zelenskyy has sacked his UK ambassador, days after he criticised the president on Sky News.

title: British man found not guilty of murdering terminally-ill wife in Cyprus but convicted of manslaughter
description: David Hunter has been found not guilty of the murder of his terminally-ill wife in Cyprus - but he was found guilty of the lesser charge of manslaughter.

title: Commentator criticised for 'sexist' remark during World Cup match
description: An Australian football presenter has been accused of making sexist remarks while commentating on one of the opening matches of the Women's World Cup.

title: 'Brutally cruel' animal market to stop selling dog and cat meat
description: A notorious animal market once touted as a tourist attraction will stop selling dog and cat meat after a celebrity-backed campaign.

title: Man, 26, who posed as school student for 54 days faces sexual assault charges
description: A 26-year-old man who posed as a high school student in the US has been charged with sexual assault.

title: 'Human remains' found in suitcase on Texas ranch
description: A suitcase containing what police believe to be human remains has been discovered on a ranch in Texas.

title: Amsterdam to ban cruise ships from city centre after launching 'stay away' campaign
description: Amsterdam has banned cruise ships from docking in the city centre in its latest attempt to cut tourism and pollution.

title: Australian sailor gives up dog who helped him survive at sea
description: After three months with only his dog Bella for company, rescued Australian sailor Timothy Shaddock has had to say goodbye to her.
